    {
      "id": "syllables",
      "icon": "🔡",
      "title": "Syllables",
      "subtitle": "Is-Sillabi — splitting words into syllables",
      "intro": "In Maltese, splitting words into syllables makes spelling easier. Rules: each syllable has only 1 vowel; the second syllable starts with a consonant; if there are 2 consonants in the middle, split between them.",
      "facts": [
        "Each syllable must have only 1 vowel.",
        "The second syllable must start with a consonant.",
        "If there are 2 consonants together in the middle, split them.",
        "Examples: ors → ors; mara → ma-ra; raġel → ra-ġel; mejda → mej-da."
      ],
      "items": [
